commit 63c11cbb386c69ad52129d3835ccd478f455694b
Author: claude-opus47-app <claude-opus47-app@anthropic.com>
Date:   Fri Apr 24 00:02:49 2026 +0800

    feat(cylinder): DEC-V61-053 Batch B1a · laminar threading + domain grow + block scaling
    
    Implements 3 of the adapter changes promised by Batch A gold YAML preconditions.
    sampleDict.cylinderCenterline + forceCoeffs axis test are split to B1b (next
    commit) for atomic reviewability.
    
    Changes in src/foam_agent_adapter.py:
    
    1. Laminar threading (lines 513-533, new ~14 LOC):
       At the BODY_IN_CHANNEL EXTERNAL dispatch site, query
       self._db.get_execution_chain(task_spec.name)["turbulence_model"] and use
       whitelist value if it's in {laminar, kOmegaSST, kEpsilon}. Falls back to
       existing _turbulence_model_for_solver heuristic otherwise. This honors
       whitelist.yaml:83 `turbulence_model: laminar` (DEC-V61-005 A-class correction)
       instead of silently overriding it to kOmegaSST.
    
    2. Domain grow in _generate_circular_cylinder_wake (4 lines changed):
         H = 2.5D → 6D        (half-height, blockage driver)
         L_inlet = 2D → 10D   (upstream, prevents blockage bias)
         L_outlet = 8D → 20D  (downstream, prevents wake-outflow feedback)
       Blockage D/(2H): 20% → ~8%. Matches Williamson 1996 unconfined context.
    
    3. Block count scaled 200×100×1 (40k) → 400×200×1 (80k):
       Preserves near-cylinder dx,dy ~0.075D, adequate for Re=100 laminar Karman
       shedding. Alternative (keep 200×100) would give dx=0.15D which is too coarse.
    
    4. 0/k, 0/omega, 0/nut conditional write (if not _is_laminar):
       Laminar solver stack doesn't register these fields; writing them when
       simulationType=laminar causes "Field nut not found" / RAS-model-not-registered
       errors at startup.
    
    5. turbulenceProperties conditional content:
       laminar → `simulationType  laminar;` (standalone)
       else    → `simulationType  RAS; RAS { RASModel ...; turbulence on; ... }`
    
    Smoke-tested both branches via bare-instance generator:
      laminar:   simtype=laminar     k=False  omega=False  nut=False  blocks=400x200  grown
      kOmegaSST: simtype=RAS         k=True   omega=True   nut=True   blocks=400x200  grown
    
    Regression: test_foam_agent_adapter.py 108/110 (2 BFS failures are pre-existing
    at a50d522, unrelated to this commit).
    
    Runtime cost: 40k → 80k cells ≈ 2x more solver iterations per timestep.
    Combined with laminar (cheaper per iter than kOmegaSST), net estimated
    runtime ~1.5-2x baseline.
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
