knowledge/gold_standards/backward_facing_step.yaml:36:      evidence_ref: "DEC-V61-052 round 2c: default RAS model is now kOmegaSST (selected via TaskSpec.boundary_conditions.turbulence_model, default 'kOmegaSST'). SST's F1/F2 blending — k-ω near the wall, k-ε in the free stream — captures the separated shear layer substantially better than standard k-ε on BFS. Measured improvement on the same mesh: kEpsilon → Xr/H=3.99 (-36.3% miss), kOmegaSST + x-graded mesh → Xr/H=5.64 (-9.9% miss, inside 10% tolerance). kEpsilon remains available as a wrong_model diagnostic."
knowledge/gold_standards/backward_facing_step.yaml:43:  contract_status: "SATISFIED — DEC-V61-052 closed all four defects V61-051 exposed (flat channel with no step; k/ε to 1e+30; misaligned Xr probe; no wall-shear measurement). The rewritten 3-block mesh produces a real BFS field (15154 pts, 0 points in step void, |U|_max=1.04·U_bulk). Round 3 (Codex r2 #1) landed the authoritative wall-shear Xr extractor: read `lower_wall` face tau_x from the allPatches VTK, find the pos→neg sign change (OpenFOAM's convention for -tau_xy on a floor where reversed flow → positive), interpolate to the zero crossing. Current fixture yields Xr/H = 5.647 via `reattachment_method: wall_shear_tau_x_zero_crossing`. Round 2a near-wall Ux proxy (Xr/H=5.647 via `near_wall_tau_x_proxy_via_Ux`) remains as a cross-check and agrees to the 4th digit. Round 2c flipped the default RAS model from kEpsilon (Xr/H=3.99, -36.3% miss) to kOmegaSST + x-graded mesh (simpleGrading 0.25 near the step corner), bringing Xr/H to 5.647 — -9.8% vs Driver 1985 = 6.26, INSIDE the 10% tolerance band. Round 2d raised endTime to 1500 and demonstrated two-fixture Xr stability across t=1000/1500 (drift +0.09%) + Ux residual plateau at t=1400→1500 (+0.1% per 100 iters). Round 2b added a structured preflight scalar-contract gate that cannot be evaded by status renaming. Solver: simpleFoam, kOmegaSST + SIMPLEC + bounded-linearUpwind + Spalding wall function, final continuity sum_local=1.30e-7 on 7360 cells. kEpsilon remains available as a `wrong_model` diagnostic via boundary_conditions.turbulence_model override. Geometry, solver convergence, and headline scalar all pass."
