  HIGH-1 · Extractor trims by sample count, not physical time. [src/cylinder_centerline_extractor.py](/Users/Zhuanz/Desktop/cfd-harness-unified/src/cylinder_centerline_extractor.py:140) uses `int(n_total * window_start_fraction)`, while the FO writes with `writeControl timeStep` and adjustable `deltaT` in [src/foam_agent_adapter.py](/Users/Zhuanz/Desktop/cfd-harness-unified/src/foam_agent_adapter.py:4895). Early small timesteps can overpopulate startup samples, so “0.5” may not mean “after t=100s”. `min_samples=4` can also pass a physically tiny window. Suggested fix: trim by time threshold `t_min + fraction*(t_max-t_min)` and require a minimum physical duration or shedding-cycle count.

  MED-1 · Domain is improved but still not “unconfined enough” for a 5% Cd/St contract. [src/foam_agent_adapter.py](/Users/Zhuanz/Desktop/cfd-harness-unified/src/foam_agent_adapter.py:4476) sets `H=6D`, i.e. blockage `D/(12D)=8.3%`; the gold doc itself still says >5% blockage biases the anchors in [knowledge/gold_standards/circular_cylinder_wake.yaml](/Users/Zhuanz/Desktop/cfd-harness-unified/knowledge/gold_standards/circular_cylinder_wake.yaml:16). Suggested fix: grow lateral half-height to at least `10D`, preferably `12D`, or explicitly carry “residual blockage risk” into B3 instead of saying it matches Williamson context.

  MED-2 · Mesh density claim is too optimistic. [src/foam_agent_adapter.py](/Users/Zhuanz/Desktop/cfd-harness-unified/src/foam_agent_adapter.py:4532) gives `dx=0.075D`, `dy=0.06D` on a uniform Cartesian/baffle cylinder. That is a 50% coarsening from the old x-spacing, not preservation, and is weak for 5% Cd/Cl/centerline wake-deficit closure. Suggested fix: target `dx <= 0.05D` near the cylinder/wake, ideally with local grading/refinement rather than only global uniform growth.

  MED-3 · Station matching ignores y/z. [src/cylinder_centerline_extractor.py](/Users/Zhuanz/Desktop/cfd-harness-unified/src/cylinder_centerline_extractor.py:153) matches only `x`, discarding `_y/_z`. That makes an off-axis sampled row look valid and can bias `ux` for a centerline observable. Suggested fix: enforce `abs(y) <= tol` and `abs(z) <= tol` or return a diagnostic when rows are not on the intended centerline.

  LOW-1 · Semantics are mostly honest, but docs still contradict the reverted rename. [knowledge/gold_standards/circular_cylinder_wake.yaml](/Users/Zhuanz/Desktop/cfd-harness-unified/knowledge/gold_standards/circular_cylinder_wake.yaml:9), [knowledge/gold_standards/cylinder_crossflow.yaml](/Users/Zhuanz/Desktop/cfd-harness-unified/knowledge/gold_standards/cylinder_crossflow.yaml:15), and [src/cylinder_centerline_extractor.py](/Users/Zhuanz/Desktop/cfd-harness-unified/src/cylinder_centerline_extractor.py:14) still say Batch B2 “will rename” / “gold YAML rename”. The later resolution text is correct. Suggested fix: remove the stale rename promise; keep the compatibility bridge wording.

OUT_OF_SCOPE_FOLLOWUPS (informational only):
  - Laminar whitelist fallback looks structurally correct: `get_execution_chain()` returns `None` for non-whitelist names, so the heuristic path remains active.
  - Extra `div(phi,k/omega)` scheme entries are likely inert in laminar because no k/omega equations are solved; I did not run OpenFOAM.
  - Add tests for irregular timestep trimming, 3-of-9 finite outliers, off-axis y/z rejection, and an adapter-generated `controlDict` filename/FO round trip.
  - Full fail on one missing station is the right comparator posture for this DEC; adding `missing_stations` diagnostics would make failures easier to debug.

SUMMARY:
B1+B2 should not close cleanly yet because the extractor windowing bug can silently average startup data. B3 is safe to enter only after the time-based trim fix and with the remaining blockage/mesh risks carried as explicit physics risks, not treated as resolved.

